    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-02-18T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-02-18T18:00:00-05:00" n="72"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d72">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/8918a</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PWH1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="1" xml:id="d72fn1">The same, <hi rend="italic">mutatis
                            mutandis</hi>, on the same date, to the Ambassador in France (No.
                        3199).</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-02-18T18:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 18, 1918, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>6611. Department has received through the Greek Legation an intimation from
                        <persName corresp="#p_VEK1">Venizelos</persName> of the desirability of the
                    Allies issuing some statement indicating their intention to stand behind Greece
                    and see that her rights are protected, and at the same time conveying an
                    expression of their appreciation of Greece’s entry into the war on the side of
                    the Allies. The Department desires to know whether the British Government has
                    received a similar message and if so intends to make any such declaration.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
